  <source>Kuopio University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In Kuopio University Hospital Department of Clinical Neurophysiology there have been designed
      a fast EEG electrode, that is suitable for acute emergency use. This study will address the
      clinical use of acute EEG with this fast EEG electrode in in- hospital patients who have been
      resuscitated due to cardiac arest. After resuscitation patients will be treated in ICU and
      EEG will be recorded for 24 hours.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
